 10 French J said at par 33: 
 'The kind of interest necessary to enliven the discretion under s 84(5) can include '... a special well-established non-proprietary connection with land or waters that is of significance to that person'.

In this regard, Mr Gamogab might seek to lead evidence that the rights and interests possessed under the traditional laws acknowledged, and the traditional customs observed, by the Torres Strait islander native title claimants: 






 76.1 have never included rights of exclusive possession of the sea or seabed; 

 76.2 have never amounted to a right to exclude the Dangaloub-Gizra from the claim area or parts of it; 

 76.3 always positively included rights of access and use possessed by the Dangaloub-Gizra; 

